  "texts": [
    "FOR INTERNET & SOC'Y, PRINCIPLED ARTIFICIAL INTELLIGENCE: MAPPING CONSENSUS IN ETHICAL AND RIGHTS-BASED APPROACHES TO PRINCIPLES FOR AI 11-12 (2020) (discussing the purpose of AI and pointing out the role of principle articulation in defining comprehensive governance norms); see also Dennis Redeker, Lex Gill & Urs Gasser, Towards Digital Constitutionalism?",
    "Mapping Attempts to Craft an Internet Bill of Rights, 80 INT'L COMMC'N GAZETTE 302, 316 (2018) (\"[I]nstead of dealing with the nuts and bolts of drafting legislation, digital constitutionalism as a societal constitutionalism allows to think about the 'ideal' Internet.",
    "The discourse thus provides an opportunity for action-oriented political philosophizing, having to collectively weight oftenconflicting rights and principles.",
    "Even if non-binding, these documents can be influential, as they become a rallying point for civil society, media and politicians, and judges can take them as a point of orientation where no legislation exists.\"",
    "(citations omitted))."
